			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Play partner is a bard and we are an amazing combo, we regularly duo HoH for good exp with no fuss.
<br />

<br />
We each do many things well and several things she does better, of course I have my specilities as well.
<br />

<br />
Bards Charm ,Mez, Lull, Haste, Slow, Heal (over time), increase resists etc etc, Bottom line a Bard can help you be better right Now.
<br />

<br />
Bards cannot buff, root, or tank and most importantly take a hi degree of concentration to play well
<br />

<br />
Both bards and rangers pull well outdoors but the bard will usually get the nod due to their more seamless crowd control skills. Plus of course bards will usually get the indoor pull work.
<br />

<br />
I first thought a Druid/Ranger combo was killer but must say Bard/Ranger is crazy good.
<br />

<br />
Oh and she does die alot more than I do, comes with pulling of course but seems more so an issue with her class as well.
<br />

<br />
Never felt like I was "outclassed", except perhaps in that she can solo quite easy and I cannot.
<br />

<br />
Sulsil Quicksilver
<br />
The Long Riders
<br />
Bristlebane</span><span class="gentblsmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Sulsil on Thu Sep 02, 2004 2:43 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
