			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I love my Bard, Bewdy - 55 VS - almost as much as my Ranger - 65 200 AA's.
<br />

<br />
When groups are hard to get and ranger soloing gets a bit old, I fire up the bard and have a ball.
<br />

<br />
Because of my time zone, I'm often the only player in a zone - and I love running the bard around the warehouse perimeter in Dulaks pulling 40 or 50 mobs and chanting them, in pairs, to death.  Huge fun and massive XP.  Had to compromise a bit if I wanted to loot too however <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />, stopping to loot with 40 mobs behind me invited a pummeling.  I'm now looking for another zone I can do this in at lvl 55.
<br />

<br />
I don't AE mobs because the song is point blank - and I am just not a good enough bard to stay a micro-metre out of melee range and yet stay within AE range.  Get hit way too much.
<br />

<br />
Bards in my opinion - are the greatest class in the game.
<br />
I love having one in my groups.
<br />

<br />
Nonetheless, I love my ranger just that little bit more.  I know I should regard all my children equally - but I can't help having a special fondness for the ranger.  He will always be my only real toon.
<br />

<br />
Lnnolanwil<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=593281" target="_blank" class="postlink">Llnolanwil</a>, 65 Ranger of Tunare, Mith Marr Server</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
